Shell Script Program
Title

Student Marks Result System

Problem Statement

Write a shell script that performs the following tasks:

Accept the name of a student.

Accept marks of 3 subjects from the user.

Calculate the total and average marks.

Display the result according to the following conditions:

Average Marks	Result
≥ 60	First Class
≥ 50 and < 60	Second Class
≥ 40 and < 50	Pass
< 40	Fail

Store the result in a file named result.txt.

Expected Output Example
Enter student name: Rahul
Enter marks for Subject 1: 70
Enter marks for Subject 2: 65
Enter marks for Subject 3: 60

Total Marks: 195
Average Marks: 65

Result: First Class

File result.txt should contain:

Student Name: Rahul
Marks: 70 65 60
Average: 65
Result: First Class
Concepts Covered

Students will practice:

read (user input)

arithmetic operations

if-elif-else

variables

file output (>> result.txt)
